arage door extension springs.";i:9;s:136:"This video will show you how to replace the extension springs on your garage doorGet your new set of Garage Door Springs on our website.";i:10;s:79:"1 Extension springs are color coated see the chart below and order accordingly.";i:11;s:17:"2 Weigh the door.";i:12;s:144:"For a single car door place a bath scale in the center of the opening remove all spring tension from the door and lower the door onto the scale.";i:13;s:243:"If your garage door has extension springs the springs stretch out as the door closes and retract as the door opens the garage door industry has released a standard color chart for the strength pull for these springs as seen in the table below.";i:14;s:97:"Many of the older extension springs may not have visible paint color on either end of the spring.";i:15;s:81:"In this video youll learn how to spot and replace a garage door extension spring.";i:16;s:71:"A few years back I narrowly avoided being hit by a spring that snapped.";i:17;s:91:"Extension springs when designed are made for a specific height and weight of a garage door.";i:18;s:101:"The end of an extension spring is also important to know and understand each end has a different use.";i:19;s:136:"When you are determining the type of extension spring for your garage door job be sure to know these factors when ordering your springs.";i:20;s:35:"Extension Garage Door Springs 7 ft.";i:21;s:48:"Light Blue Extension Spring 2588 Select options.";i:22;s:98:"Heavy Duty Replacement Extension Garage Door Spring Stretch Spring 2-Pack110 lb 45 out of 5 stars.";i:23;s:29:"Get it as soon as Mon Aug 16.";i:24;s:24:"FREE Shipping by Amazon.";i:25;s:57:"This door would use two 210 pound lift extension springs.";i:26;s:119:"Or if the door has four extension springs the door would use two 100 pound lift springs and two 110 pound lift springs.";i:27;s:119:"A more accurate method for weighing either a torsion spring door or an extension spring door is on our YouTube channel.";i:28;s:42:"Extension springs for 7 tall garage doors.";i:29;s:147:"These are 25-42s 25 long with 42 of stretch 12 of 7 All have double loop ends with the exception of the 200 210 220 springs they have clipped ends.";i:30;s:54:"We highly recommend that you replace springs in pairs.";i:31;s:144:"The first step in weighing a garage door with extension springs is to disconnect the operator arm from the door if you have an opener installed.";i:32;s:71:"To do so you can disengage the pin from the systems attachment bracket.";i:33;s:55:"Do NOT simply just pull the red emergency release cord.";i:34;s:48:"Doing so could lead to an incorrect measurement.";i:35;s:120:"Extension springs are an older garage door technology that uses a 2-spring system placed at each end of the garage door.";i:36;s:182:"Homebuilders like them because they are an easier and less expensive garage system to install but they tend to be more costly for homeowners to maintain than a torsion spring system.";i:37;s:126:"Extension springs run parallel to the tracks of the door and are typically situated between the tracks and the garage ceiling.";i:38;s:133:"Extension springs store energy by extending while the door is closing and then releasing the stored energy while the door is opening.";i:39;s:29:"Garage Door Extension Spring.";i:40;s:36:"MSRP May Vary Depending on Location.";i:41;s:27:"25 x 110 White Black Boxed.";i:42;s:25:"Buy Online Find in Store.";i:43;s:43:"How to order garage door extension springs.";i:44;s:146:"You will need to know the height and weight of your door to order replacement springs and then select the type of spring ends best fit your needs.";i:45;s:70:"Measure the height of your door from bottom to top of the door panels.";i:46;s:40:"66-75 - choose 7ft 76 - 82 - choose 8ft.";i:47;s:109:"Garage doors are heavy so they have garage door springs which make the process of opening an effortless task.";i:48;s:129:"Garage door torsion springs and garage door extension springs are two types of springs that can be used in garage door operation.";i:49;s:175:"DURA-LIFT 90 - 180 Pound Heavy-Duty Extension Garage Door Spring 2-Packs are extension spring replacements for broken sectional garage door extension springs for 7 tall doors.";i:50;s:176:"All DURA-LIFT garage door extension springs are manufactured from oil-tempered spring wire meeting ASTM A229 and are designed for a minimum of 10000 door open and close cycles.";i:51;s:35:"Double-looped ends are standard to.";i:52;s:225:"Extension springs the other kind of garage door springs are torsion springs run alongside the upper garage door tracks the ones that run parallel to the ceiling and stretch or extend out and back to help lift the garage door.";i:53;s:106:"Following are the steps necessary to replace one or more of these springs while taking safety precautions.";}}